# Real Features, No Simulated Bandaids

When a user wants to **actually use or test a real feature** (Tap to Pay, hardware, native capability, physical device), do **NOT** add simulated/fallback/mock alternatives.

- ❌ Don't add "Use simulated reader for testing"
- ❌ Don't add mock/stub modes as a workaround
- ❌ Don't suggest "you can test the flow with X instead"

Instead, help them get the **real thing** working:
- Debug why it's not working (Expo Go vs dev build, simulator vs device, permissions, config)
- Fix the actual blockers
- Provide clear steps for real setup

Only suggest simulated/mock when the user explicitly asks for a testing fallback or says they can't use the real hardware yet.
